There are two Types:
1- break;
2- continue;


1- ////  break    ////

this statement used to break the flow of the control loop, Its used only within the loop, then it will terminate the loop
- It will bring the flow out of the "nearest loop".
- its used to get out from a loop if a certain condition happened 
Ex.

void main()
{
  int i = 1;
  while (i < 20)
  {
    print ("This loop number $i");
    i++;
    if(i == 4)
    {
      print("the loop will break after it");
      break;
    }
  }
}


2-  ////  Continue  ////
continue will skip this iterate and continue from the next one

Ex.
void main()
{
  int i = 1;
  while (i < 20)
  {
    print("This Loop number $i");
    i++;
    if(i == 4)
    {  
      print("The loop 4 Skipped");
      continue;
    }
  }
}
